# CarePoint 365 Project Conventions

## Language
- Always write in UK English (colour, behaviour, organisation, cancelled, etc.)

## Tech Stack
- React 19 + TypeScript (strict mode)
- Vite 7 for build tooling
- Tailwind CSS 4 for styling
- Zustand for client state
- TanStack React Query for server state
- React Router 7 for routing
- React Hook Form + Zod for forms
- MSAL for Azure AD authentication
- Microsoft Dataverse Web API for backend

## Architecture Patterns
- Functional components only (class components only for error boundaries)
- Custom hooks for reusable logic and data fetching
- Lazy-loaded route-level code splitting with React.lazy + Suspense
- Error boundaries at app, route, and feature level
- Barrel exports via index.ts in each module directory

## Import Conventions
Use `@/` path alias for all src imports:
```typescript
import { useAuth } from '@/hooks/useAuth';
import { Button } from '@/components/common/Button';
import type { ShiftViewData } from '@/api/dataverse/types';
```

## Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (`ShiftCard.tsx`)
- Hooks: camelCase with `use` prefix (`useRotaData.ts`)
- Utilities: camelCase (`formatDate.ts`)
- Types/Interfaces: PascalCase (`interface StaffRow {}`)
- Constants: SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE
- Event handlers: `handle` prefix (`handleClick`)
- Callback props: `on` prefix (`onClick`)
- Booleans: `is`/`has`/`can`/`should` prefix
